Portions of margo are ported from niri. As of margo 0.7.4 these are the
three hand-rolled Wayland protocol implementations, adapted to margo's
state/tag model:

  - margo/src/protocols/wlr_foreign_toplevel.rs   (from niri's protocols/foreign_toplevel.rs, wlr half)
  - margo/src/protocols/ext_workspace.rs          (from niri's protocols/ext_workspace.rs)
  - margo/src/protocols/virtual_pointer.rs         (from niri's protocols/virtual_pointer.rs)

margo additionally borrows architectural patterns from niri (frame-callback
scheduling, hotplug handling, the screencast portal shape, transactional
resize). Those are reimplementations, not copied code; the files above are
the portions derived from niri source and covered by this notice.

niri is GPL-3.0-or-later and margo is GPL-3.0-or-later, so the two are
license-compatible.
